		<content> .... and returned to Cardenden. Joe   
 Corrie decided to pursue a careere in 
 writing and did so until his death in 
 1968. His writing portrayed the social
 consqueces of ecomomic depression,    
 unemployment and industrial strife in 
 the '20s and 30s. In light of the     
 industrial strife in the minning      
 communite in 1984-85 his work has     
 acquired a new significance and his   
 play "In Time of Strife" is presently 
 played throughout Scotland by the     
 7:84 Theatre Company.                 
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
